-Whene you create a repo you can add a readme file 
-the readme file is about sharing note and steps how to use or how to setup the project
-the readme file will have the extention " .md " this mean " MarkDown " it a language you can use it to 
edite your texte in the readme file 
-EX: 
# A first-level heading
## A second-level heading
### A third-level heading

this link is to sherche more about markdown language in wikipidia : 
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Markdown


this link if you want to learn more about how to writ a good Documentation in github readme file : 
https://docs.github.com/fr/get-started/writing-on-github/getting-started-with-writing-and-formatting-on-github/basic-writing-and-formatting-syntax

How to clone a repo to your local computer : 
1. go to the repo
2. presse the button " <> Code "
3. copy the link
4. create a file where you will put this project
5. open cmc and write : 
mkdir project > to create a folder named by project
cd project > to enter this folder
git clone <link> to clone the repo here



